The area covered in the survey is situated in the south_eastern area of the{Wakefield Metropolitan District {Council}. It encompasses the villages of{South Elmsall, South Kirkby & {Moorthorpe and Upton.}
The villages are historically mining hamlets in an area which is predominantly agricultural.The majority of people are employed by the NCB, work on the local industrial estate or in the nearby towns of {Barnsley, Doncaster, Pontefract or {Wakefield.
Employment prospects in the area for the future look poor. Over the past five years 40% of young people have had to leave the area to seek employment.
